{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JVcAbCU9qJYx7czWaen78D","type":"tool_result","content":"   650â†’\n   651â†’| Flag | Description |\n   652â†’|------|-------------|\n   653â†’| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   654â†’| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   655â†’| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n   656â†’\n   657â†’Without `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n   658â†’\n   659â†’### `cloche poll`\n   660â†’\n   661â†’```\n   662â†’cloche poll <run-id>\n   663â†’```\n   664â†’\n   665â†’Block until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n   666â†’\n   667â†’### `cloche stop`\n   668â†’\n   669â†’```\n   670â†’cloche stop <run-id>\n   671â†’```\n   672â†’\n   673â†’### `cloche delete`\n   674â†’\n   675â†’```\n   676â†’cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   677â†’```\n   678â†’\n   679â†’Delete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n   680â†’\n   681â†’### `cloche health`\n   682â†’\n   683â†’```\n   684â†’cloche health\n   685â†’```\n   686â†’\n   687â†’Show per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n   688â†’\n   689â†’### `cloche workflow`"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4f4a76a6-d5ff-4a04-aa47-bd20b66a7dff","uuid":"d817290c-0967-4d85-9929-1d969c49e274","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n\nWithout `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n\n### `cloche poll`\n\n```\ncloche poll <run-id>\n```\n\nBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n\n### `cloche stop`\n\n```\ncloche stop <run-id>\n```\n\n### `cloche delete`\n\n```\ncloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n```\n\nDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n\n### `cloche health`\n\n```\ncloche health\n```\n\nShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n\n### `cloche workflow`","numLines":40,"startLine":650,"totalLines":856}}}
